 A = \{x\in \mathbb{N}：  q\mid x  \wedge x< pq\}
B = \{y\in \mathbb{N}：  p\mid y  \wedge y< pq\}
 \left| A \right| = p-1, \left| B \right| =q-1
A \cup B \subseteq G. 
A \cap B \neq \emptyset. 
z \in A \cap B.
z \geq pq.
\phi(pq) = pq-1 - (p-1) -(q-1)
\varphi(pq)=\varphi(p)\varphi(q)=(p-1)(q-1)
